==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Exauthorate
<hw>Ex*au"thor*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>exauctoratus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>exauctorare</ets> to dismiss;
<ets>ex</ets> out + <ets>auctorare</ets> to bind to something, to hire,
fr. <ets>auctor</ets>. See <er>Author</er>.]</ety> <def>To deprive of
authority or office; to depose; to discharge.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Exauthorated</qex> for their unworthiness.</q> <rj><qau>Jer.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exauthoration</ent>⟦br⟧
